cs.MA, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is likely because the paper considers a multi-server system where jobs are assigned to servers based on a selection rule. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is likely because the paper deals with job assignment in a cluster of shared servers, which is a common problem in networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is likely because the paper deals with a cluster of shared servers and proposes schemes to reduce the mean sojourn time of jobs in the system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is likely because the paper proposes two schemes to optimize the job assignment process in a multi-server system. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is likely because the paper analyzes the system operating under the proposed schemes as $N \to \infty$ and establishes the existence and uniqueness of stationary solution of the mean field.
